This guide covers basic plotting functions in R using base R only (no ggplot2 or external libraries).

ðŸ§© 1. Basic Plot Syntax
plot(x, y,
     main = "Main Title",
     xlab = "X-axis Label",
     ylab = "Y-axis Label",
     col = "color",
     pch = symbol,
     type = "plot_type",
     lwd = line_width,
     lty = line_type)

ðŸ”¹ Common Parameters:
Parameter	Description
x, y	Numeric vectors for x and y axes
main	Plot title
xlab, ylab	Labels for X and Y axes
col	Color of points/lines
pch	Point shape (0â€“25), e.g. 16 = filled circle
type	Type of plot: "p" = points, "l" = lines, "b" = both, "o" = overplotted, "h" = histogram lines
lwd	Line width
lty	Line type: 1 = solid, 2 = dashed, 3 = dotted, etc.
